TITLE: Defining Address Schema Properties in JSX
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines various properties of an address schema using JSX components. It includes fields for personal information, address details, and validation options. Each SchemaItem component represents a property with its type, description, and constraints.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/reference/api/create-shipment.api.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_65

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
<SchemaItem
  collapsible={false}
  name={"email"}
  required={false}
  schemaName={"string"}
  qualifierMessage={undefined}
  schema={{"type":"string","nullable":true,"description":"The party email"}}
>

</SchemaItem>
```

