TITLE: Scheduling a Pickup with Karrio API in Python
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to schedule a pickup using the Karrio API. It includes creating a PickupRequest object with necessary details like pickup date, address, and time windows, then sending the request and parsing the response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/carriers/sdk/pickup.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import karrio
from karrio.core.models import PickupRequest

request = PickupRequest(...)

pickup, messages = karrio.Pickup.schedule(request).from_(carrier_gateway).parse()
```

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import karrio
from karrio.core.models import PickupRequest, Address

address = Address(
    postal_code="V6M2V9",
    city="Vancouver",
    country_code="CA",
    state_code="BC",
    address_line1="5840 Oak St"
)

request = karrio.Pickup.schedule(
    PickupRequest(
        pickup_date="2015-01-28",
        address=address,
        instruction="Door at Back",
        ready_time="15:00",
        closing_time="17:00",
        options={"loading_dock_flag": True},
    )
)

pickup, messages = request.from_(carrier_gateway).parse()
```

