TITLE: Updating a Shipment with JavaScript/Node.js
DESCRIPTION: Updates a shipment's properties using the Karrio API with JavaScript/Node.js. This example demonstrates how to update a shipment's label type, reference, payment information, options, and metadata.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/reference/api/update-shipment.api.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import Karrio from '@karrio/sdk';

const karrio = new Karrio.default({
  host: 'https://api.karrio.io',
  apiKey: 'API_KEY'
});

const request = {
  shipment_identifier: 'shp_c0a5c06c6c55458997b67dd7ad56e740',
  shipment: {
    label_type: 'PDF',
    reference: 'my-reference',
    payment: {
      paid_by: 'sender',
      currency: 'CAD',
      account_number: '2343253'  
    },
    options: {
      shipment_date: '2022-09-12'
    },
    metadata: {
      source: 'web'
    }
  }
};

const response = await karrio.proxy.shipments.update(request);

console.log(response.data);
```

