TITLE: Submitting Orders using karrio API - Bash
DESCRIPTION: This curl request demonstrates how to submit new order data to the karrio API. It requires an API key for authorization and expects JSON-formatted order details in the request body. It returns a response including order identification and details on transaction status.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/product/orders.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl --request POST \
  --url https://api.karrio.io/v1/orders \
  --header 'Authorization: Token [API_KEY]' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
	"source": "Shopify",
	"order_id": "450789469",
	"order_date": "2008-01-10",
	"shipping_to": {
		"address_line1": "123 Amoebobacterieae St",
		"city": "Ottawa",
		"country_code": "CA",
		"email": "bob.norman@mail.example.com",
		"person_name": "Bob Bobsen",
		"phone_number": "555-625-1199",
		"postal_code": "K2P0V6",
		"state_code": "ON"
	},
	"line_items": [
		{
			"quantity": 1,
			"sku": "IPOD-342-N",
			"title": "IPod Nano",
			"description": "IPod Nano - Pink",
			"origin_country": "CA",
			"value_amount": "199.99",
			"value_currency": "USD",
			"weight": 0.5,
			"weight_unit": "KG"
		}
	]
}'
```

