TITLE: Transforming Python Code with Karrio Codegen
DESCRIPTION: The 'transform' command is used to convert Python code generated by quicktype into code that uses attrs and jstruct decorators. Essential imports are adjusted, and 'Type' is optionally appended to class names. It handles complex type annotations and ensures no duplicate imports. Key command flags allow customization of class name suffixes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/modules/cli/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
# Transform from stdin to stdout
cat input.py | karrio codegen transform > output.py

# Transform from file to file
karrio codegen transform input.py output.py

# Transform from file to stdout
karrio codegen transform input.py

# Disable appending 'Type' to class names
karrio codegen transform input.py output.py --no-append-type-suffix
```

