TITLE: Configuring Success Response Schema
DESCRIPTION: This snippet creates a details component for displaying the schema of a successful response from the webhook testing API. The schema includes operation and success properties, each defined with its data type and description.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/reference/api/test-webhook.api.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
<details
  style={{}}
  className={"openapi-markdown__details response"}
  data-collapsed={false}
  open={true}
>
  <summary
    style={{}}
    className={"openapi-markdown__details-summary-response"}
  >
    <strong>
      Schema
    </strong>
  </summary><div
    style={{"textAlign":"left","marginLeft":"1rem"}}
  >

  </div><ul
    style={{"marginLeft":"1rem"}}
  >
    <SchemaItem
      collapsible={false}
      name={"operation"}
      required={true}
      schemaName={"string"}
      qualifierMessage={undefined}
      schema={{"type":"string","description":"Operation performed"}}
    >

    </SchemaItem><SchemaItem
      collapsible={false}
      name={"success"}
      required={true}
      schemaName={"boolean"}
      qualifierMessage={undefined}
      schema={{"type":"boolean","description":"Specify whether the operation was successful"}}
    >

    </SchemaItem>
  </ul>
</details>
```

