TITLE: Address Schema Definition in JSON
DESCRIPTION: Defines a comprehensive address schema including country codes, contact information, address details, and validation options. Includes enums for country codes and length constraints for various fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/reference/api/retrieve-shipment.api.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_40

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "country_code": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["AC", "AD", "AE", "AF", "AG", "AI", "AL", "AM", "AN", "AO", "AR"],
      "description": "The address country code"
    },
    "email": {
      "type": "string",
      "nullable": true,
      "description": "The party email"
    },
    "phone_number": {
      "type": "string",
      "nullable": true,
      "maxLength": 20,
      "description": "The party phone number."
    },
    "state_code": {
      "type": "string",
      "nullable": true,
      "maxLength": 20,
      "description": "The address state code"
    },
    "residential": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "nullable": true,
      "default": false,
      "description": "Indicate if the address is residential or commercial (enterprise)"
    },
    "validate_location": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "nullable": true,
      "default": false,
      "description": "Indicate if the address should be validated"
    },
    "object_type": {
      "type": "string",
      "default": "address",
      "description": "Specifies the object type"
    }
  }
}
```

