TITLE: Defining Pickup Schema Item: Package Location
DESCRIPTION: Defines the schema for the 'package_location' property, which specifies where the package(s) can be found at the pickup site. This optional property has a maximum length of 50 characters and is nullable.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/reference/api/schedule-pickup.api.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
<SchemaItem
          collapsible={false}
          name={"package_location"}
          required={false}
          schemaName={"string"}
          qualifierMessage={"**Possible values:** `<= 50 characters`"}
          schema={{"type":"string","nullable":true,"description":"The package(s) location.<br/>
        eg: Behind the entrance door.
        ","maxLength":50}}
        >

        </SchemaItem>
```

