TITLE: Defining Shipment Object Schema in JSON
DESCRIPTION: This schema defines the structure of a shipment object, including properties for metadata, messages, status, and carrier information. It specifies data types, descriptions, and possible values for various fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/reference/api/cancel-order.api.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_62

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": {},
    "default": {},
    "description": "User metadata for the shipment"
  },
  "messages": {
    "type": "array",
    "items": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "message": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "The error or warning message"
        },
        "code": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "The message code"
        },
        "details": {
          "type": "object",
          "additionalProperties": {},
          "description": "any additional details"
        },
        "carrier_name": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "The targeted carrier"
        },
        "carrier_id": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "The targeted carrier name (unique identifier)"
        }
      }
    },
    "description": "The list of note or warning messages"
  },
  "status": {
    "enum": ["draft", "purchased", "cancelled", "shipped", "in_transit", "delivered", "needs_attention", "out_for_delivery", "delivery_failed"],
    "type": "string",
    "default": "draft",
    "description": "The current Shipment status"
  },
  "carrier_name": {
    "type": "string",
    "nullable": true,
    "description": "The shipment carrier"
  }
}
```

