TITLE: Sending GraphQL Requests with cURL
DESCRIPTION: This bash script demonstrates how to send a GraphQL request to the Karrio Management API using cURL.  It sets the necessary headers, including the 'Authorization' header with the API key and the 'Content-Type' header to 'application/json'.  The `--data-raw` option is used to pass the GraphQL query and variables in the request body.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/reference/management/overview.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
"curl --request POST \
  --url 'https://api.karrio.io/graphql' \
  --header 'Authorization: Token  [API_KEY]' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data-raw $'{\"query\":\"mutation mutate_system_connection($data: SystemCarrierMutationInput\u0021) {\\n  mutate_system_connection(input: $data) {\\n    carrier {\\n      id\\n      active\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\",\"variables\":{\"data\":{\"id\":\"car_773f4a5577e4471e8918a9a1d47b208b\",\"enable\":false}}}\' \
  --compressed"
```

