TITLE: Defining Schema Items for API Response - React
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines several SchemaItem components that represent parts of an API response schema including message, code, and details. Each schema specifies types and descriptions for validation purposes. It uses React prop types for defining properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/reference/api/pickup-cancel.api.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
<SchemaItem
  collapsible={false}
  name={"message"}
  required={false}
  schemaName={"string"}
  qualifierMessage={undefined}
  schema={{"type":"string","description":"The error or warning message"}}
>
</SchemaItem>

<SchemaItem
  collapsible={false}
  name={"code"}
  required={false}
  schemaName={"string"}
  qualifierMessage={undefined}
  schema={{"type":"string","description":"The message code"}}
>
</SchemaItem>

<SchemaItem
  collapsible={true}
  className={"schemaItem"}
>
  <details
    style={{}}
    className={"openapi-markdown__details"}
  >
    <summary
      style={{}}
    >
      <span
        className={"openapi-schema__container"}
      >
        <strong
          className={"openapi-schema__property"}
        >
          details
        </strong><span
          className={"openapi-schema__name"}
        >
           object
        </span>
      </span>
    </summary><div
      style={{"marginLeft":"1rem"}}
    >
      <div
        style={{"marginTop":
        ".5rem","marginBottom":
        ".5rem"}}
      >

        any additional details

      </div><SchemaItem
        name={"property name*"}
        required={false}
        schemaName={"any"}
        qualifierMessage={undefined}
        schema={{"type":"object","additionalProperties":{},"description":"any additional details"}}
        collapsible={false}
        discriminator={false}
      >

      </SchemaItem>
    </div>
  </details>
</SchemaItem>
```

