TITLE: Drawing a Curved Path in SVG
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a curved path using the `path` element in SVG.  The `d` attribute specifies the path data using quadratic Bezier curves (`Q`).  The path's appearance is styled with stroke color and miter limit.  The stroke color uses the CSS variable `--ifm-font-color-base`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/karrioapi/karrio/blob/main/apps/www/docs/reference/guides/shipments.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: SVG
CODE:
```
<path
        d="M 200 480 Q 300 450 320 405 Q 340 360 320 300 Q 300 240 320 190 Q 340 140 419.03 110.56"
        fill="none"
        stroke="var(--ifm-font-color-base)"
        strokeMiterlimit={10}
        pointerEvents="stroke"
      />
      <path
        d="M 423.95 108.73 L 418.61 114.45 L 419.03 110.56 L 416.17 107.89 Z"
        fill="rgba(0, 0, 0, 1)"
        stroke="var(--ifm-font-color-base)"
        strokeMiterlimit={10}
        pointerEvents="all"
      />
```

